21
00:02:16,300 --> 00:02:24,241
# #

22
00:02:59,544 --> 00:03:01,077
Mrs. Pope?

23
00:03:03,748 --> 00:03:05,248
Tom.

24
00:03:05,249 --> 00:03:06,817
Tommy Wills.

25
00:03:06,818 --> 00:03:08,352
How are you?

26
00:03:08,353 --> 00:03:09,520
(Maggie)
I'm good.

27
00:03:09,521 --> 00:03:11,888
Oh, gosh,
it's good to see you.

28
00:03:11,889 --> 00:03:13,590
What brings you to town?

29
00:03:13,591 --> 00:03:15,559
I'm just visiting my folks
for a few days.

30
00:03:15,560 --> 00:03:17,060
Hi, there.

31
00:03:17,061 --> 00:03:18,862
Hey. Mrs. Pope, I want
to introduce you to my wife.

32
00:03:18,863 --> 00:03:19,896
This is Linda.

33
00:03:19,897 --> 00:03:21,198
Hi.
- Maggie.

34
00:03:21,199 --> 00:03:22,232
Nice
to meet you.

35
00:03:22,233 --> 00:03:23,300
Nice to meet you.

36
00:03:23,301 --> 00:03:25,669
Congratulations.
I heard about the wedding.

37
00:03:25,670 --> 00:03:27,304
Oh, thank you.

38
00:03:27,305 --> 00:03:28,706
So how do you all
know each other?

39
00:03:28,707 --> 00:03:30,341
Well--

40
00:03:30,342 --> 00:03:32,409
Um, Tom knew my son.

41
00:03:32,410 --> 00:03:33,910
Oh, do I know him?

42
00:03:33,911 --> 00:03:35,846
No.

43
00:03:35,847 --> 00:03:37,848
<i>[loud crash]</i>

44
00:03:37,849 --> 00:03:39,216
<i>(woman)</i>
<i>Help me!</i>

45
00:03:39,217 --> 00:03:40,351
<i>Help me.</i>

46
00:03:40,352 --> 00:03:41,752
Stay back.
Stay back.

47
00:03:41,753 --> 00:03:43,220
<i>Give her space.</i>

48
00:03:43,221 --> 00:03:44,321
Watch her head.

49
00:03:44,322 --> 00:03:45,489
Someone,
call 911.

50
00:03:45,490 --> 00:03:47,391
<i>Hold her head up.</i>
<i>Hold her head.</i>

51
00:03:47,392 --> 00:03:49,926
<i>Call 911 now!</i>

52
00:03:49,927 --> 00:03:51,628
<i>It's okay;</i>
<i>hold her head up.</i>

53
00:03:53,765 --> 00:03:55,699
Yes, we need an ambulance
at Glen Owl Market.

54
00:03:55,700 --> 00:03:58,435
<i>There's a girl</i>
<i>having a seizure.</i>

55
00:03:58,436 --> 00:04:00,237
<i>Okay.</i>
<i>All right.</i>

56
00:04:00,238 --> 00:04:01,238
<i>(woman)</i>
<i>There she goes.</i>

57
00:04:01,239 --> 00:04:02,439
<i>Just take deep breaths.</i>

58
00:04:02,440 --> 00:04:03,674
<i>Honey, you're doing</i>
<i>just fine.</i>

59
00:04:03,675 --> 00:04:04,908
<i>(Linda)</i>
<i>Are they coming?</i>

60
00:04:04,909 --> 00:04:07,578
<i>They're on their way.</i>

61
00:04:16,921 --> 00:04:19,490
<i>[approaching siren wailing]</i>

62
00:04:54,158 --> 00:04:55,492
(man)
She got in here

63
00:04:55,493 --> 00:04:57,428
before I had a chance to see
what they dropped off.

64
00:04:57,429 --> 00:04:59,095
I'm going
to find Hope.

65
00:04:59,096 --> 00:05:00,697
I don't know
where the hell she is,

66
00:05:00,698 --> 00:05:02,299
but I'm gonna find her,
I swear to you.

67
00:05:02,300 --> 00:05:03,700
Let's try this
one more time.

68
00:05:03,701 --> 00:05:04,768
Where is she?

69
00:05:04,769 --> 00:05:07,170
I don't know
where Hope is.

70
00:05:07,171 --> 00:05:09,372
[laughs]

71
00:05:09,373 --> 00:05:12,175
Come on, Red.

72
00:05:12,176 --> 00:05:13,644
<i>It's me.</i>

73
00:05:13,645 --> 00:05:15,879
I told you
everything I know.

74
00:05:15,880 --> 00:05:17,414
Okay, Carl, untie him.

75
00:05:19,150 --> 00:05:20,584
Let the man have a drink.

76
00:05:28,827 --> 00:05:31,662
Thank you.

77
00:05:31,663 --> 00:05:33,229
Can I have a smoke?

78
00:05:33,230 --> 00:05:35,298
Well, I don't see
why not.

79
00:05:47,378 --> 00:05:49,746
Okay, tough guy.

80
00:05:52,149 --> 00:05:53,750
Where is she?

81
00:05:55,887 --> 00:05:57,788
[screaming]

82
00:06:00,324 --> 00:06:03,259
[dramatic music]

83
00:06:03,260 --> 00:06:11,201
# #

84
00:06:23,681 --> 00:06:26,449
(man)
Baby sister,

85
00:06:26,450 --> 00:06:28,785
There's never going to be
a better time to sell.

86
00:06:28,786 --> 00:06:31,187
I don't want to sell.

87
00:06:31,188 --> 00:06:33,156
Look, there's a window
of opportunity right now.

88
00:06:33,157 --> 00:06:34,758
It's my home.

89
00:06:34,759 --> 00:06:37,594
I raised my family there.

90
00:06:37,595 --> 00:06:39,095
John Stanton
at the bank says

91
00:06:39,096 --> 00:06:41,164
that that road
is going to come through.

92
00:06:41,165 --> 00:06:45,869
And he's got a developer
who will pay us cash tomorrow

93
00:06:45,870 --> 00:06:47,337
if we sell together.

94
00:06:47,338 --> 00:06:50,240
I don't know why we're talking
about this again.

95
00:06:50,241 --> 00:06:53,744
You do what you want
with your part.

96
00:06:53,745 --> 00:06:55,979
Mary Margaret,
make sense.

97
00:06:55,980 --> 00:06:59,016
I mean, that development's
going to happen

98
00:06:59,017 --> 00:07:00,183
whether we like it
or not.

99
00:07:00,184 --> 00:07:03,620
I am going to sell
my half.

100
00:07:03,621 --> 00:07:06,690
But we can get triple
if we both sell.

101
00:07:10,294 --> 00:07:13,363
Is this what you want
or what Nancy Kaye wants?

102
00:07:16,434 --> 00:07:18,835
It's what we both want.

103
00:07:18,836 --> 00:07:24,641
Look, I'm just trying to do
what's best for you,

104
00:07:24,642 --> 00:07:26,843
what's best
for all of us.

105
00:07:26,844 --> 00:07:30,614
Think about moving
where me and Nancy Kaye live.

106
00:07:30,615 --> 00:07:33,050
I mean, there's
a great subdivision.

107
00:07:33,051 --> 00:07:37,520
Got three-bedroom houses
with central air and a pool.

108
00:07:37,521 --> 00:07:40,523
It's manageable, honey.

109
00:07:40,524 --> 00:07:42,492
And you might meet
somebody.

110
00:07:42,493 --> 00:07:44,995
[chuckles]

111
00:07:44,996 --> 00:07:47,464
How long's it been
since you danced?

112
00:07:47,465 --> 00:07:53,804
Do you remember
when you loved to dance?

113
00:07:53,805 --> 00:07:56,172
I don't want to sell,
George.

114
00:07:56,173 --> 00:07:57,207
<i>(woman)</i>
<i>Hoo-hoo!</i>

115
00:07:58,509 --> 00:07:59,509
Look who's here.

116
00:07:59,510 --> 00:08:00,844
<i>(Nancy Kaye)</i>
<i>Howdy hi.</i>

117
00:08:00,845 --> 00:08:03,113
<i>The prices down here</i>
<i>are so cheap.</i>

118
00:08:03,114 --> 00:08:05,082
You two got finished
with your little talk?

119
00:08:05,083 --> 00:08:06,883
I don't like getting involved
in discussions

120
00:08:06,884 --> 00:08:08,051
involving money.

121
00:08:08,052 --> 00:08:09,419
I don't have a head
for finances,

122
00:08:09,420 --> 00:08:11,922
do I, Georgie?

123
00:08:11,923 --> 00:08:13,724
Oh, Maggie,
you look tired.

124
00:08:13,725 --> 00:08:15,025
You know what you need?

125
00:08:15,026 --> 00:08:17,027
Let me see.
A manicure.

126
00:08:17,028 --> 00:08:19,997
Oh, yeah,
brighten up your day.

127
00:08:19,998 --> 00:08:21,098
Hey, you know what?

128
00:08:21,099 --> 00:08:22,198
We got to get going

129
00:08:22,199 --> 00:08:23,867
if we're going to get
to clogging tonight.

130
00:08:23,868 --> 00:08:25,168
We got to practice.

131
00:08:25,169 --> 00:08:28,005
These trophies just don't
win themselves, you know.

132
00:08:28,006 --> 00:08:29,439
Well, come on.
Up and at 'em.

133
00:08:33,210 --> 00:08:35,812
Think about it,
pumpkin.

134
00:08:35,813 --> 00:08:39,516
I'm just thinking
about your interest.

135
00:08:43,655 --> 00:08:45,822
You know, we really ought
to do these little lunches

136
00:08:45,823 --> 00:08:48,358
more than once
every couple months.

137
00:08:48,359 --> 00:08:49,392
Really.

138
00:08:49,393 --> 00:08:51,128
Come on, Georgie.
Bye-bye.

139
00:08:51,129 --> 00:08:53,063
Good-bye.

140
00:08:59,603 --> 00:09:02,039
Hope!

141
00:09:23,961 --> 00:09:26,563
My mom says
I have to go with you.

142
00:09:34,304 --> 00:09:37,507
Come on; we got to go now.

143
00:09:37,508 --> 00:09:40,009
<i>Let's go!</i>

144
00:09:48,786 --> 00:09:51,588
What happened to your face?

145
00:09:56,994 --> 00:09:58,795
Where are we going?

146
00:10:03,333 --> 00:10:06,903
<i>[man speaking on radio]</i>

147
00:10:06,904 --> 00:10:11,408
<i>...in Memphis, Tennessee,</i>
<i>home of the cave.</i>

148
00:10:24,588 --> 00:10:26,823
Why are we stopping?

149
00:10:39,069 --> 00:10:40,870
Hang on, kid.

150
00:12:40,024 --> 00:12:42,491
Wake up.

151
00:12:45,195 --> 00:12:47,496
I'm hungry.

152
00:12:52,970 --> 00:12:55,738
[line ringing]

153
00:12:55,739 --> 00:12:57,874
<i>[Hope on recording] Hey, it's Hope.</i>
<i>Leave a message.</i>

154
00:12:57,875 --> 00:12:59,676
Beep!

155
00:12:59,677 --> 00:13:03,345
Where are you?

156
00:13:33,443 --> 00:13:36,112
<i>What the fuck are you doing?</i>

157
00:13:37,247 --> 00:13:38,414
You're doin' it.

158
00:13:38,415 --> 00:13:40,083
What the fuck are you doing?
Give me that.

159
00:13:40,084 --> 00:13:41,117
No!

160
00:13:41,118 --> 00:13:43,419
Give that to me!
- No!

161
00:13:45,789 --> 00:13:48,324
[engine turns over]

162
00:13:51,394 --> 00:13:54,396
[siren wailing]

163
00:13:54,397 --> 00:13:56,332
God damn it.

164
00:14:04,207 --> 00:14:07,110
Shit.

165
00:14:07,111 --> 00:14:09,245
Pretend like you're sick.

166
00:14:09,246 --> 00:14:11,580
I think I am.

167
00:14:12,750 --> 00:14:16,085
License and registration,
please.

168
00:14:16,086 --> 00:14:17,854
Just a sec, Officer.

169
00:14:19,589 --> 00:14:21,090
[groans]

170
00:14:25,696 --> 00:14:28,631
You must be
in one hell of a rush.

171
00:14:28,632 --> 00:14:29,666
Kid's sick.

172
00:14:29,667 --> 00:14:31,367
I got to get him
to a doctor.

173
00:14:31,368 --> 00:14:34,236
What happened
to your face?

174
00:14:34,237 --> 00:14:37,073
Well, it's--

175
00:14:37,074 --> 00:14:39,542
It's a long story...

176
00:14:39,543 --> 00:14:41,544
Jennifer.

177
00:14:41,545 --> 00:14:44,013
Hi, Billy.
- Hi.

178
00:14:45,716 --> 00:14:47,717
Nice uniform.

179
00:14:47,718 --> 00:14:49,552
What brings you home?

180
00:14:49,553 --> 00:14:51,054
[sighs]

181
00:14:51,055 --> 00:14:53,790
Just need a little vacation.

182
00:14:53,791 --> 00:14:54,891
You still in Detroit?

183
00:14:54,892 --> 00:14:56,125
No, Memphis.

184
00:14:56,126 --> 00:14:57,160
Wow.

185
00:14:57,161 --> 00:14:58,561
Just playing
with my band.

186
00:14:58,562 --> 00:14:59,929
How's that going?

187
00:14:59,930 --> 00:15:03,733
It's going good.
It's great.

188
00:15:03,734 --> 00:15:06,836
Who's your friend?

189
00:15:06,837 --> 00:15:08,270
<i>(Billy)</i>
<i>This is Clayton.</i>

190
00:15:08,271 --> 00:15:09,538
I know his mom.

191
00:15:09,539 --> 00:15:11,708
I'm keeping him
for a while.

192
00:15:11,709 --> 00:15:12,975
Hi, Clayton.

193
00:15:12,976 --> 00:15:15,078
Hi.

194
00:15:15,079 --> 00:15:16,545
How long you around?

195
00:15:18,082 --> 00:15:22,785
Oh, couple days.

196
00:15:22,786 --> 00:15:24,754
How you been?

197
00:15:24,755 --> 00:15:27,023
Good.

198
00:15:29,793 --> 00:15:31,828
Well, I guess
I ought to let you go.

199
00:15:31,829 --> 00:15:33,896
Clayton, tell this guy
if he doesn't stop speeding,

200
00:15:33,897 --> 00:15:35,598
he's going to have
to let you do the driving

201
00:15:35,599 --> 00:15:37,499
from now on.

202
00:15:41,371 --> 00:15:43,572
Maybe I'll see you
while I'm here.

203
00:15:43,573 --> 00:15:46,075
Yeah, maybe.

204
00:15:49,780 --> 00:15:51,180
<i>(Billy)</i>
<i>What's wrong with you?</i>

205
00:15:51,181 --> 00:15:52,949
<i>I said, "act sick."</i>

206
00:15:52,950 --> 00:15:54,150
You sounded
like you were having a baby.

207
00:16:11,135 --> 00:16:12,168
Filter
for your tractor.

208
00:16:12,169 --> 00:16:13,269
Oh, thanks, Roy.

209
00:16:13,270 --> 00:16:14,703
Could you check
my oil?

210
00:16:14,704 --> 00:16:16,739
The engine's been running
a little hot lately.

211
00:16:16,740 --> 00:16:19,842
You bet.

212
00:16:21,211 --> 00:16:22,511
Want to pop the hood?

213
00:16:22,512 --> 00:16:25,181
Oh.

214
00:16:25,182 --> 00:16:27,083
I'm going to get a coke.
You want one?

215
00:16:27,084 --> 00:16:29,118
No, thanks.

216
00:16:36,226 --> 00:16:38,995
Do I need any?

217
00:16:38,996 --> 00:16:41,998
Uh, no.
It's good.

218
00:16:41,999 --> 00:16:43,800
Thanks, Roy.

219
00:16:43,801 --> 00:16:45,467
Put it on my bill.

220
00:16:45,468 --> 00:16:47,503
<i>Okay.</i>

221
00:17:34,017 --> 00:17:36,052
Yoo-hoo!

222
00:17:36,053 --> 00:17:38,120
Billy?

223
00:17:38,121 --> 00:17:39,588
[sighs]

224
00:17:39,589 --> 00:17:43,159
[television playing
electronic noises]

225
00:17:43,160 --> 00:17:44,160
[silence]

226
00:17:44,161 --> 00:17:45,328
[television playing]

227
00:17:45,329 --> 00:17:46,329
[silence]

228
00:17:46,330 --> 00:17:47,897
<i>(Clayton)</i>
<i>Hey.</i>

229
00:17:47,898 --> 00:17:49,031
I was watching that.

230
00:17:50,767 --> 00:17:52,201
Billy?

231
00:17:58,708 --> 00:18:00,476
Billy, what are you doing here?

232
00:18:00,477 --> 00:18:02,144
<i>Why didn't you tell me</i>

233
00:18:02,145 --> 00:18:03,812
you were coming?

234
00:18:03,813 --> 00:18:05,047
Hi, Mom.

235
00:18:05,048 --> 00:18:07,750
Who's that little boy
in the living room?

236
00:18:07,751 --> 00:18:10,586
Got any of that pimento cheese
you used to make?

237
00:18:10,587 --> 00:18:12,788
<i>No, I don't make it</i>
<i>anymore.</i>

238
00:18:12,789 --> 00:18:14,257
You were the only one
who ate it.

239
00:18:14,258 --> 00:18:17,093
If I'd known you were coming,
I could have made some.

240
00:18:17,094 --> 00:18:19,828
Billy, who is that boy?

241
00:18:19,829 --> 00:18:21,697
That's Clayton.

242
00:18:21,698 --> 00:18:23,165
I'm keeping him
for a while.

243
00:18:23,166 --> 00:18:26,903
That doesn't really answer
my question.

244
00:18:26,904 --> 00:18:30,606
What happened
to the cedar tree out front?

245
00:18:30,607 --> 00:18:31,807
It was struck by lightning.

246
00:18:31,808 --> 00:18:33,609
Billy.

247
00:18:33,610 --> 00:18:34,643
What is with you?

248
00:18:34,644 --> 00:18:36,712
Will you look at me?

249
00:18:42,886 --> 00:18:45,054
[sighs]

250
00:18:45,055 --> 00:18:47,023
What happened?

251
00:18:47,024 --> 00:18:48,357
Nothing. I'm just trying
to make a sandwich.

252
00:18:48,358 --> 00:18:50,159
I'm starving.

253
00:18:50,160 --> 00:18:51,294
Excuse me.

254
00:18:51,295 --> 00:18:53,529
I haven't heard from you
in over a year,

255
00:18:53,530 --> 00:18:56,132
and you show up
with a banged-up face and a kid,

256
00:18:56,133 --> 00:18:58,100
and I'm not supposed
to ask any questions?

257
00:18:58,101 --> 00:19:00,303
Sorry to inconvenience you.

258
00:19:00,304 --> 00:19:02,871
I just need a place to stay
for a couple days.

259
00:19:02,872 --> 00:19:03,872
Is that okay?

260
00:19:03,873 --> 00:19:05,774
This is your home too.

261
00:19:05,775 --> 00:19:07,609
It always has been.

262
00:19:07,610 --> 00:19:08,644
Better put something on that.

263
00:21:02,192 --> 00:21:04,660
<i>[Maggie crying]</i>

264
00:21:40,330 --> 00:21:43,098
She said I was supposed
to wake you up for supper.

265
00:22:09,025 --> 00:22:11,093
Are you going
someplace?

266
00:22:11,094 --> 00:22:12,261
Yeah, I got
to go out.

267
00:22:12,262 --> 00:22:13,796
I got stuff to do.

268
00:22:13,797 --> 00:22:17,065
Billy.

269
00:22:17,066 --> 00:22:19,902
Can you watch
the kid?

270
00:22:19,903 --> 00:22:21,537
[sighs]
Sure.

271
00:22:21,538 --> 00:22:22,871
(Billy)
Thank you.

272
00:22:22,872 --> 00:22:24,740
<i>I'll be back later.</i>

273
00:22:29,546 --> 00:22:32,080
You can stay in here.

274
00:22:35,251 --> 00:22:36,919
I'll be downstairs
if you need me.

275
00:23:31,842 --> 00:23:36,011
[Brahms' <i>Hungarian Dance No. 5]</i>

276
00:23:36,012 --> 00:23:38,213
<i>[man talking]</i>

277
00:23:38,214 --> 00:23:39,348
<i>(man)</i>
<i>...thanks to surgery</i>

278
00:23:39,349 --> 00:23:41,350
at the hospital
for sick children.

279
00:23:41,351 --> 00:23:46,689
# #

280
00:23:46,690 --> 00:23:49,057
Your TV sucks.

281
00:23:49,058 --> 00:23:51,193
Then why are you watching it?

282
00:23:51,194 --> 00:23:54,196
There's nothing else to do.

283
00:23:54,197 --> 00:23:56,665
Why don't you read a book?

284
00:23:56,666 --> 00:23:58,701
Don't have one.

285
00:23:58,702 --> 00:24:06,575
# #

286
00:25:02,398 --> 00:25:03,866
<i>(woman)</i>
<i>It's been a long time coming.</i>

287
00:25:03,867 --> 00:25:05,534
<i>I'm determined,</i>

288
00:25:05,535 --> 00:25:07,235
more than ever this time.

289
00:25:07,236 --> 00:25:12,374
<i>And I know it won't be easy,</i>
<i>but I have a baby now.</i>

290
00:25:12,375 --> 00:25:13,576
And...

291
00:25:13,577 --> 00:25:15,878
<i>I got to do it.</i>

292
00:25:15,879 --> 00:25:18,547
I'm Tanya,
and I'm an alcoholic.

293
00:25:18,548 --> 00:25:20,816
(all)
Thanks for sharing, Tanya.

294
00:25:23,319 --> 00:25:27,523
Is there anyone else
who'd like to share?

295
00:25:32,496 --> 00:25:34,530
No, I'll pass.

296
00:25:36,132 --> 00:25:37,299
Okay, then.

297
00:25:37,300 --> 00:25:39,735
<i>Well, let's join hands.</i>

298
00:25:46,776 --> 00:25:47,776
Whose father?

299
00:25:47,777 --> 00:25:49,011
(all)
Our father,

300
00:25:49,012 --> 00:25:52,381
who art in heaven,
hallowed by thy name.

301
00:25:52,382 --> 00:25:54,316
Thy kingdom come.

302
00:25:54,317 --> 00:25:57,920
Thy will be done on earth
as it is in heaven.

303
00:25:57,921 --> 00:26:00,756
Give us this day
our daily bread,

304
00:26:00,757 --> 00:26:02,424
and forgive us our trespasses

305
00:26:02,425 --> 00:26:06,028
as we forgive those
who trespass against us.

306
00:26:06,029 --> 00:26:08,497
How often you go?

307
00:26:08,498 --> 00:26:10,499
Not so much anymore.

308
00:26:10,500 --> 00:26:12,367
First year,
I went religiously.

309
00:26:12,368 --> 00:26:15,070
Now I just go
when I need to.

310
00:26:15,071 --> 00:26:16,839
Yeah, me too.

311
00:26:18,975 --> 00:26:22,377
What happened
to New York?

312
00:26:22,378 --> 00:26:24,413
I thought you were going
to be on Broadway.

313
00:26:24,414 --> 00:26:25,781
[laughs]

314
00:26:25,782 --> 00:26:27,816
Yeah, so did I.

315
00:26:27,817 --> 00:26:29,117
I went.

316
00:26:29,118 --> 00:26:32,655
I waitressed for two years
before my dad got sick.

317
00:26:32,656 --> 00:26:34,557
None of my brothers
were around anymore,

318
00:26:34,558 --> 00:26:38,093
so I came home
to take care of him.

319
00:26:38,094 --> 00:26:40,629
That was ten years ago.

320
00:26:42,566 --> 00:26:45,968
You ever wish
you'd gone back?

321
00:26:45,969 --> 00:26:47,903
Not really.

322
00:26:47,904 --> 00:26:52,274
I'm good at what I do,
and I like it here, so...

323
00:26:54,578 --> 00:26:57,580
How long you been sober?

324
00:26:57,581 --> 00:26:59,281
A long time.

325
00:26:59,282 --> 00:27:01,316
Wasn't so much I had
a problem, you know.

326
00:27:01,317 --> 00:27:03,919
It was more about
where I was headed.

327
00:27:03,920 --> 00:27:05,921
You know how it is.

328
00:27:05,922 --> 00:27:08,724
Yeah, I do know
how it is.

329
00:27:11,194 --> 00:27:13,161
How long
you really been sober?

330
00:27:13,162 --> 00:27:14,997
<i>(man)</i>
<i>Billy!</i>

331
00:27:14,998 --> 00:27:16,899
Hey, man,
is that you?

332
00:27:16,900 --> 00:27:17,833
Rick?

333
00:27:17,834 --> 00:27:19,668
Hey, hey, rock star!

334
00:27:19,669 --> 00:27:21,103
Hey, man.
How you been doing?

335
00:27:22,171 --> 00:27:23,205
Sorry, man.

336
00:27:23,206 --> 00:27:25,741
I haven't seen you
since forever.

337
00:27:25,742 --> 00:27:28,344
I know.
How's Donny?

338
00:27:28,345 --> 00:27:30,579
He died.

339
00:27:30,580 --> 00:27:31,580
What?

340
00:27:31,581 --> 00:27:32,648
Yeah, you didn't hear?

341
00:27:32,649 --> 00:27:33,682
He died, man.

342
00:27:33,683 --> 00:27:35,384
Drove his truck
off a bridge.

343
00:27:35,385 --> 00:27:37,786
Man, he was wasted.

344
00:27:37,787 --> 00:27:41,056
Oh, my God.
- Yeah.

345
00:27:41,057 --> 00:27:42,157
That must have
wrecked Shelly.

346
00:27:42,158 --> 00:27:44,393
Oh, man,
it was brutal.

347
00:27:44,394 --> 00:27:46,428
I mean, she got two kids,
and one of 'em is his,

348
00:27:46,429 --> 00:27:50,065
So, you know,
it's rough, man.

349
00:27:50,066 --> 00:27:52,901
Hey, you want to--you want
to go grab a drink?

350
00:27:52,902 --> 00:27:55,137
You want to get a beer
or something, man?

351
00:27:55,138 --> 00:27:56,204
Man, I can't.

352
00:27:56,205 --> 00:27:57,873
Maybe later.

353
00:27:57,874 --> 00:28:01,143
Oh, I got you.

354
00:28:01,144 --> 00:28:04,112
Police business, huh?

355
00:28:04,113 --> 00:28:05,981
See you, Billy.

356
00:28:05,982 --> 00:28:08,817
Always nice to see you
outside the squad car, Rick.

357
00:28:14,824 --> 00:28:17,225
[laughs]

358
00:28:38,014 --> 00:28:40,916
<i>What time is it?</i>

359
00:28:40,917 --> 00:28:42,284
It's late.

360
00:28:42,285 --> 00:28:44,252
Where've you been?

361
00:28:44,253 --> 00:28:49,325
I had some things
I needed to take care of.

362
00:28:49,326 --> 00:28:51,427
You smell like a bar.

363
00:28:51,428 --> 00:28:54,262
<i>He's not</i>

364
00:28:54,263 --> 00:28:55,230
A stray dog, Billy.

365
00:28:58,468 --> 00:28:59,835
What?

366
00:28:59,836 --> 00:29:02,538
He's not one of those strays
you used to bring home.

367
00:29:02,539 --> 00:29:04,640
What are you talking about?

368
00:29:04,641 --> 00:29:10,278
The ones that I ended up
taking care of.

369
00:29:11,348 --> 00:29:14,149
Turn out the lights
before you come up.

370
00:29:28,998 --> 00:29:31,199
<i>[woman over telephone]</i>
<i>Billy, where are you?</i>

371
00:29:31,200 --> 00:29:32,534
I'm in my mom's house.

372
00:29:32,535 --> 00:29:33,635
Look, Beth,
I just need to know

373
00:29:33,636 --> 00:29:35,371
if you've heard anything
from Hope.

374
00:29:35,372 --> 00:29:37,406
<i>I haven't heard anything</i>
<i>since she blew out of here.</i>

375
00:29:37,407 --> 00:29:40,609
Well, do you have any idea
where she could be?

376
00:29:40,610 --> 00:29:41,677
<i>I have no idea.</i>

377
00:29:41,678 --> 00:29:46,348
<i>I thought she was with you.</i>

378
00:29:46,349 --> 00:29:47,983
She never checked in.

379
00:29:47,984 --> 00:29:49,785
I mean, if I don't hear from her
in the next couple of days,

380
00:29:49,786 --> 00:29:53,722
then maybe I'll just--
I don't know--go back there.

381
00:29:53,723 --> 00:29:55,056
<i>You can't come back.</i>

382
00:29:55,057 --> 00:29:57,192
<i>Red's been asking</i>
<i>a lot of questions.</i>

383
00:29:57,193 --> 00:29:58,427
He's going to fucking kill you.

384
00:29:58,428 --> 00:29:59,995
Hold on a second.

385
00:29:59,996 --> 00:30:01,363
Could you stop?

386
00:30:01,364 --> 00:30:03,665
<i>Do something else?</i>
<i>Bzzz?</i>

387
00:30:05,535 --> 00:30:06,769
What kind of questions?

388
00:30:06,770 --> 00:30:09,271
<i>Where you are,</i>
<i>where Hope is.</i>

389
00:30:09,272 --> 00:30:11,072
<i>Billy, I don't want</i>
<i>to be involved.</i>

390
00:30:11,073 --> 00:30:12,674
<i>Last night, Leo called,</i>

391
00:30:12,675 --> 00:30:15,143
<i>and Red had me lie for him</i>
<i>and say he wasn't there.</i>

392
00:30:15,144 --> 00:30:17,145
Uh, yeah, I get it.
I get it.

393
00:30:17,146 --> 00:30:19,381
Um, well,
that's great.

394
00:30:19,382 --> 00:30:20,482
What are the dates,
again?

395
00:30:20,483 --> 00:30:22,584
<i>Billy?</i>

396
00:30:22,585 --> 00:30:25,287
Yeah, no, I'm available, sure.

397
00:30:25,288 --> 00:30:26,288
<i>Billy?</i>

398
00:30:26,289 --> 00:30:27,389
Shit, I need the work.

399
00:30:27,390 --> 00:30:28,490
<i>Is Clayton with you?</i>

400
00:30:28,491 --> 00:30:29,691
Okay, well, great.

401
00:30:29,692 --> 00:30:31,259
I understand.
<i>Listen to me--</i>

402
00:30:31,260 --> 00:30:32,861
<i>(Billy) Well, thank you.</i>
<i>I'll see you then.</i>

403
00:30:32,862 --> 00:30:35,431
Okay, thank you.
<i>- Billy!</i>

404
00:30:36,533 --> 00:30:38,300
Fucking idiot.

405
00:30:42,505 --> 00:30:44,406
I'll be back before supper.

406
00:30:44,407 --> 00:30:46,809
<i>(Maggie)</i>
<i>Okay.</i>

407
00:30:46,810 --> 00:30:48,510
Clayton?

408
00:30:48,511 --> 00:30:50,178
Run and get a clean shirt.

409
00:30:53,716 --> 00:30:55,317
You don't have one?

410
00:30:55,318 --> 00:30:57,285
Mm-mm.

411
00:30:57,286 --> 00:30:58,420
I saw you had a bag.

412
00:30:58,421 --> 00:31:00,255
Don't you have
any clothes in it?

413
00:31:00,256 --> 00:31:01,824
No.

414
00:31:01,825 --> 00:31:03,391
Do you have a toothbrush?

415
00:31:03,392 --> 00:31:05,393
Mm-mm.

416
00:31:13,470 --> 00:31:16,505
Might help
if you use this.

417
00:31:25,849 --> 00:31:27,516
What's in there?

418
00:31:30,052 --> 00:31:33,221
We don't go in there.

419
00:32:25,341 --> 00:32:26,642
<i>(Maggie) If you know how to fix</i>
<i>a tractor,</i>

420
00:32:26,643 --> 00:32:28,877
I could sure use some help.

421
00:32:48,330 --> 00:32:50,599
Hi.

422
00:32:50,600 --> 00:32:52,067
What are you doing here?

423
00:32:52,068 --> 00:32:55,971
Just thought I'd stop by
and say hi.

424
00:32:55,972 --> 00:32:57,940
Okay.

425
00:33:07,483 --> 00:33:09,117
So what's wrong?

426
00:33:11,387 --> 00:33:14,289
I need to find someone.

427
00:33:14,290 --> 00:33:17,559
Who are you looking for?

428
00:33:17,560 --> 00:33:20,896
The kid I'm with,
I need to find his mother.

429
00:33:20,897 --> 00:33:25,601
Well, have you tried
her friends, family?

430
00:33:25,602 --> 00:33:27,402
No one knows where she is.

431
00:33:27,403 --> 00:33:31,239
Does she have a husband
or a boyfriend?

432
00:33:33,343 --> 00:33:35,844
What about the boy's father?

433
00:33:44,887 --> 00:33:47,456
Why doesn't Billy look like you?

434
00:33:47,457 --> 00:33:49,424
'cause he looks like his father.

435
00:33:49,425 --> 00:33:50,625
Why did you name him Billy?

436
00:33:50,626 --> 00:33:51,793
<i>'Cause his father's name</i>
<i>was that</i>

437
00:33:51,794 --> 00:33:54,096
and his father before him.

438
00:33:54,097 --> 00:33:55,663
Hey, could you get
the jumper cables?

439
00:33:55,664 --> 00:33:57,665
Sure.

440
00:34:04,140 --> 00:34:06,308
Where are they?

441
00:34:06,309 --> 00:34:09,344
Oh, they died
a long time ago.

442
00:34:11,547 --> 00:34:13,748
My mom goes to work every day.

443
00:34:13,749 --> 00:34:15,417
Where does she work?

444
00:34:15,418 --> 00:34:16,818
Hooters.

445
00:34:16,819 --> 00:34:18,286
Oh!

446
00:34:18,287 --> 00:34:20,522
She's a dancer.

447
00:34:20,523 --> 00:34:22,090
<i>Is that right?</i>

448
00:34:22,091 --> 00:34:23,125
Mm-hmm.

449
00:34:23,126 --> 00:34:25,593
Okay, now,
take this cable,

450
00:34:25,594 --> 00:34:27,095
and put it
right in there.

451
00:34:28,464 --> 00:34:30,332
<i>Attaboy.</i>

452
00:34:39,642 --> 00:34:42,010
Haven't seen one of these
in a while.

453
00:34:42,011 --> 00:34:43,412
'68?

454
00:34:43,413 --> 00:34:45,514
That's right.

455
00:34:45,515 --> 00:34:47,549
What can I do for you?

456
00:34:47,550 --> 00:34:49,617
Brakes keep on slipping.

457
00:34:49,618 --> 00:34:51,319
Let's have a look.

458
00:35:09,338 --> 00:35:12,574
Boy, she's walked a mile.

459
00:35:12,575 --> 00:35:14,242
She still plays good.

460
00:35:14,243 --> 00:35:15,577
I'm kind of partial to her.

461
00:35:17,913 --> 00:35:19,448
You're Maggie pope's boy,
aren't you?

462
00:35:20,883 --> 00:35:22,350
You know my mom?

463
00:35:22,351 --> 00:35:23,751
I'm Roy Long.

464
00:35:23,752 --> 00:35:25,320
Billy.

465
00:35:28,191 --> 00:35:30,692
Yeah, I got some buddies
I play with.

466
00:35:30,693 --> 00:35:33,228
We're not very good,
but we have fun.

467
00:35:33,229 --> 00:35:34,696
<i>(man)</i>
<i>Car's ready.</i>

468
00:35:34,697 --> 00:35:36,264
<i>Just needed some fluid.</i>

469
00:35:38,634 --> 00:35:40,302
What do I owe you?

470
00:35:40,303 --> 00:35:41,803
Just brake fluid.

471
00:35:41,804 --> 00:35:43,238
Five bucks
ought to cover it.

472
00:35:49,112 --> 00:35:50,712
Come back on Sunday,

473
00:35:50,713 --> 00:35:51,879
<i>2:00.</i>

474
00:35:51,880 --> 00:35:54,282
<i>We can always use</i>
<i>another player.</i>

475
00:36:00,490 --> 00:36:02,491
Hop in the truck,
Clayton.

476
00:36:02,492 --> 00:36:04,759
I'll be right back.

477
00:36:12,201 --> 00:36:14,035
Get out of the back, Clayton.

478
00:36:14,036 --> 00:36:15,703
Get out of the back!

479
00:36:15,704 --> 00:36:17,038
Why?

480
00:36:17,039 --> 00:36:18,039
Thud!

481
00:36:18,040 --> 00:36:19,073
Come on. Come on. Come on.

482
00:36:19,074 --> 00:36:20,142
Get out.

483
00:36:20,143 --> 00:36:21,610
Because I said so;
that's why.

484
00:36:21,611 --> 00:36:22,910
Get out!
- I can do it myself.

485
00:36:38,093 --> 00:36:41,029
I'm sorry, Clayton.

486
00:37:06,589 --> 00:37:09,090
<i>(Billy)</i>
<i>What are you doing in here?</i>

487
00:37:09,091 --> 00:37:10,925
Nothin'.

488
00:37:10,926 --> 00:37:14,396
Is that your shirt?

489
00:37:14,397 --> 00:37:16,731
No.

490
00:37:16,732 --> 00:37:17,765
Where'd you get it?

491
00:37:17,766 --> 00:37:19,634
Maggie gave it to me.

492
00:37:23,439 --> 00:37:26,675
Soup's on.

493
00:37:39,788 --> 00:37:41,323
Did you wash
your hands?

494
00:37:41,324 --> 00:37:42,591
Yeah.

495
00:37:42,592 --> 00:37:44,826
With soap?

496
00:37:44,827 --> 00:37:46,595
Mm-hmm.

497
00:37:46,596 --> 00:37:48,730
Let me see.

498
00:37:52,201 --> 00:37:53,968
Scoot.

499
00:37:53,969 --> 00:37:55,470
[laughs]

500
00:37:55,471 --> 00:37:57,305
What are you laughing at?

501
00:37:59,542 --> 00:38:01,976
Go wash.

502
00:38:06,915 --> 00:38:08,883
<i>[Billy talking]</i>

503
00:38:08,884 --> 00:38:10,184
<i>"Scoot.</i>
<i>Wash your hands."</i>

504
00:38:10,185 --> 00:38:12,153
Wash your hands.

505
00:38:12,154 --> 00:38:14,088
<i>(Billy)</i>
<i>I'm washing 'em.</i>

506
00:38:15,991 --> 00:38:18,393
<i>If she asks you if you washed</i>
<i>your hands from now on,</i>

507
00:38:18,394 --> 00:38:19,494
<i>you just say, "yes."</i>

508
00:38:19,495 --> 00:38:21,396
<i>(Clayton)</i>
<i>Stop hogging the water.</i>

509
00:38:21,397 --> 00:38:23,431
<i>(Billy)</i>
<i>Relax.</i>

510
00:38:23,432 --> 00:38:26,000
Oh, wait.

511
00:38:26,001 --> 00:38:28,570
Here. Here.

512
00:38:33,342 --> 00:38:34,542
<i>Okay?</i>

513
00:38:34,543 --> 00:38:37,979
<i>Hold on. Here.</i>

514
00:38:40,015 --> 00:38:41,849
<i>Let me see.</i>

515
00:38:41,850 --> 00:38:44,519
<i>Other side.</i>

516
00:38:47,790 --> 00:38:50,692
He's yours, isn't he?

517
00:38:59,034 --> 00:39:00,402
Does he know?

518
00:39:02,305 --> 00:39:03,938
I don't think so.

519
00:39:10,245 --> 00:39:13,014
[sighs]

520
00:39:15,618 --> 00:39:17,652
Why didn't you tell me?

521
00:39:17,653 --> 00:39:22,256
I just found out
just a couple days ago.

522
00:39:22,257 --> 00:39:26,994
His mother's got some problems
that she needs to figure out.

523
00:39:37,440 --> 00:39:41,108
So I'm a grandmother.

524
00:39:41,109 --> 00:39:42,677
<i>[knocking at window]</i>

